50|$|Sodium metabisulfite or sodium pyrosulfite (IUPAC spelling; Br. E. sodium {{metabisulphite}} or <b>sodium</b> <b>pyrosulphite)</b> is an inorganic compound of chemical formula Na2S2O5. The substance is {{sometimes referred to}} as disodium metabisulfite. It is used as a disinfectant, antioxidant and preservative agent.|$|E

